reviews.review_text: Good solid 80's show, but ... There's nothing spectacular here.  No outstanding song versions, no long, exploratory jams.  Jerry's guitar is too quiet, which is especially noticeable on FOTM and The Other One, and the Playin' jam seems tepid.  It's a hot Other One, and a bit longer than mid-80's.

good show greaty soundboard as stated kind of your typical set tunes here but its a very good solidly played showed. Masterpiece always one of my favorites and I love Althea.  Charles Miller soundboards are so clean love them.  You can usually hear each member of the band very clear. It all depends on the tapes that he is given and the quality of them.  I really enjoyed listening to these two show 4/5 and 4/6.  Dave Lemieux  recommended these shows on his show on Sirius XM.

Hidden Gem I go with four stars for a solid 1989 show with excellent sound quality.  The gem is the beautiful combination of PITB into Built to Last.  I've heard that there were varying degrees of planning that went into song choices, but this one feels like it dropped out of the sky.  Pretty original
